from doyle howard r doyle subject re broken rib in article jc write fell about week ago down into the hold of the boat and break or crack a rib and wrench and bruise my back and leave arm my question i have be to a doctor and wa tell that it wa best to do nothing and it would heal up with no long term effect and indeed i be about better however the work i do be very hard and i be still not able to go back to work the thing that worry me be the movement or clunk i feel and hear back there when i move certain way i hear some one talk about the rib they break year ago and that it still bother them any opinion ymy doctor be right it be best to do nothing beside take some pain medication initially some patient do like thi and expect or demand to have something do in these case some physician will tape the patient put a lot of heavy adhesive tape around the chest or prescribe an elastic binder all thi do be make it harder to breath but the patient do feel cheat because soemthing be be do about the problem either way the end result be the same howard doyle doyle 